Remember when we only had a couple tries to get a good pic? I really love those days. A perfect pic was so hard to achieve that a roll of 24 shots was a great reminder that life is profoundly imperfect. If you were lucky you’d get one with everyone looking. My Mama didn’t wait around to get the perfect pic. In fact she has few pics of all of us together because she let us run around and be in the moment. The ones she does are always a little silly, a little blurry, half smiles, half cries, chocolate faces and unbrushed hair. She gave us freedom, let us be wild, loved us endlessly and we got the pictures to prove it. I love you Mama. Happy Mothers Day! @goldiehawn ❤️☀️❤️

A Sicilian Lemon Tart featuring the limited-edition spatula I designed with Rani Rose for @nokidhungry x @williamssonoma! 🍋💛 Help end childhood hunger in America by purchasing one using the link in my bio. Each spatula purchased can help provide 40 meals for kids and teens! Recipe below👇 

Crust:
1/4 cup olive oil
1 1/2 Tbsp Ground Almonds
1 1/4 cup all-purpose flour
1/4 vanilla bean sea salt
1 egg yolk

Custard:
Juice of 3 lemons
Zest of 1 lemon
6 oz. Cane sugar
2 Tsp cornstarch
2 egg yolks
2 whole eggs
2 oz of unsalted butter, cubed
2 Tbsp olive oil

1. Mix all ingredients for the crust in a bowl. Should be crumbly, but come together,
2. Press into the tart pan and bake at 350F for 15 mins. Let cool while you work on the custard.
3. Combine all ingredients for the custard in a medium sauce pan, EXCEPT FOR olive oil and butter, on medium heat. Stir until thickened.
4. Remove mixture from heat then stir in olive oil and butter until melted.
5. Pour the custard mixture onto the tart crust.
6. Refrigerate for 2-3 hours. Garnish with fresh citrus and mint.

Around our home lately 🎄 I love the holidays so much and throughout the years have collected trees, Santa’s, music boxes, snow villages, ornaments, and more. We bake, cook, sing, share laughs and create light to shine everywhere, we wish for love and peace. I am a lover of this time over year and soak every minute of it up. I guess that is a good metaphor for how I feel about life and celebrating our time here. It’s as fleeting as the holidays. Here today, gone tomorrow. So I choose to make it sweet and cozy. Everyday. And of course every Holiday. Wishing sweet and cozy to everyone ❤️💫🫶💫❤️ PS. More decorations and cozy to come 😉
